  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9, 10. at the beginning, and since the time that I commanded judges—that is, including the whole period from Joshua to Saul.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I tell thee that the Lord will build thee an house—This was the language of Nathan himself, who was specially directed to assure David, not only of personal blessing and prosperity, but of a continuous line of royal descendants.",
        "children": []
